\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces  Teaser results on two challenging low-light scenes. Each row shows the low-light input, our rendering, and the normal-light ground truth. For the rendered and ground-truth images, a red rectangle marks a representative local region, and the corresponding zoomed patch is attached to the lower-right corner for direct comparison. Our method restores visibility, preserves local structures, and produces more natural colors under severe under-exposure. For a detailed qualitative comparison of the multiple methods, see Figure~\ref {fig:qualitative_results}. }}{1}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:teaser}{{1}{1}{Teaser results on two challenging low-light scenes. Each row shows the low-light input, our rendering, and the normal-light ground truth. For the rendered and ground-truth images, a red rectangle marks a representative local region, and the corresponding zoomed patch is attached to the lower-right corner for direct comparison. Our method restores visibility, preserves local structures, and produces more natural colors under severe under-exposure. For a detailed qualitative comparison of the multiple methods, see Figure~\ref {fig:qualitative_results}}{figure.1}{}}
